			<div class="post-339 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-aging-issues">
				<!-- title, meta, and date info -->
				<div class="title clearfix">
					<div class="post-title">
						<h3 id="post-339"><a href="http://demographicsgoldmine.com/most-seniors-want-to-stay-in-their-homes-with-in-home-health-care-for-as-long-possible-but-our-senior-care-industry-wants-just-the-opposite">Most seniors want to stay in their homes with in home health care for as long possible but our senior care industry wants just the opposite.</a></h3>
					</div>
					
					<div class="author-meta">
						by <span class="meta-author"><a href="http://demographicsgoldmine.com/author/Bob Scardamalia" title="Bob Scardamalia">Bob Scardamalia</a></span>					</div>
					
					<div class="post-meta">
						<span class="month">November</span>
						<span class="day">9<span class="day-suffix">th</span><span class="day-comma">,</span></span>
						<span class="year">2012</span><br />
					</div>
					</div>
				
				<!-- "Read More" link -->
				<div class="post-content">
					<p>The survey estimates vary but AARP and others studying our older population note that between 75 and 90 percent of our seniors want to stay home.  There’s an inherent conflict here that isn’t always keeping the wishes of people in the forefront.  </p>
<p>I attended a forum hosted by the <a href="http://www.albanyguardiansociety.org">Albany Guardian Society</a> yesterday titled The Village Movement: Supporting Seniors at Home.  What an education!  Look around you and you’ll find senior residences, from assisted living to nursing homes, sprouting up like weeds.  We Baby Boomers have hit age 65 and the industry knows it.  The Village model is a community approach to aging that provides to its members everything from concierge services to health and wellness programs and social and cultural opportunities.<br />
<img src="http://demographicsgoldmine.com/images/oldercouple.jpg" alt="Senior Walk" /><br />
Image courtesy of Simon Howden at FreeDigitalPhotos.net<br />
 <a href="http://demographicsgoldmine.com/most-seniors-want-to-stay-in-their-homes-with-in-home-health-care-for-as-long-possible-but-our-senior-care-industry-wants-just-the-opposite#more-339" class="more-link">Read More&rarr;</a></p>
				</div>
				
				<!-- categories, tags and comments -->
				<div class="meta-bottom clearfix">
					<div class="alignleft"><span class="categories">Categories <a href="http://demographicsgoldmine.com/category/aging-issues" title="View all posts in Aging Issues" rel="category tag">Aging Issues</a></span><br />
					<span class="comments">Comments <a href="http://demographicsgoldmine.com/most-seniors-want-to-stay-in-their-homes-with-in-home-health-care-for-as-long-possible-but-our-senior-care-industry-wants-just-the-opposite#respond" title="Comment on Most seniors want to stay in their homes with in home health care for as long possible but our senior care industry wants just the opposite.">(0)</a></span>					</div>
