			<div class="post-323 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-census-data category-demographics-2">
				<!-- title, meta, and date info -->
				<div class="title clearfix">
					<div class="post-title">
						<h3 id="post-323"><a href="http://demographicsgoldmine.com/have-you-been-focusing-on-the-baby-boom-market-all-these-years-three-ways-to-stay-on-top-of-markets">Have you been focusing on the Baby Boom market all these years? Three ways to stay on top of markets.</a></h3>
					</div>
					
					<div class="author-meta">
						by <span class="meta-author"><a href="http://demographicsgoldmine.com/author/Bob Scardamalia" title="Bob Scardamalia">Bob Scardamalia</a></span>					</div>
					
					<div class="post-meta">
						<span class="month">November</span>
						<span class="day">5<span class="day-suffix">th</span><span class="day-comma">,</span></span>
						<span class="year">2012</span><br />
					</div>
					</div>
				
				<!-- "Read More" link -->
				<div class="post-content">
					<p>The Baby Boom generation has breached the beginning age of retirement at 65.  Born between 1946 and 1964 the Baby Boom totaled nearly 76 million births.  From entering kindergarten to entering the labor force to buying homes (and second homes) and now to retirement, the Baby Boom has impacted every social institution along its aging pathway.  Today, concerns about the financial stability of Social Security, trends in disability, health care costs and the supply of caregivers are all driven by the coming explosion in population over the age of 65.</p>
<p>The ending of the Baby Boom in 1964 was a result of economic expansion, high levels of women’s labor force participation and college enrollment and changing lifestyles.  Fertility rates plummeted ushering in the “Baby Bust”, the Gen X folks, where births fell from 4.2 million per year to only 3.4 million per year.  Communities struggled with what to do with all those elementary school classrooms built to accommodate the Baby Boomers.  This rapid decline in births and size of the following generation continued to keep the attention on the Boomers and their needs.  That focused attention on the Boomers continues today. <a href="http://demographicsgoldmine.com/have-you-been-focusing-on-the-baby-boom-market-all-these-years-three-ways-to-stay-on-top-of-markets#more-323" class="more-link">Read More&rarr;</a></p>
				</div>
				
				<!-- categories, tags and comments -->
				<div class="meta-bottom clearfix">
					<div class="alignleft"><span class="categories">Categories <a href="http://demographicsgoldmine.com/category/census-data" title="View all posts in Census Data" rel="category tag">Census Data</a>, <a href="http://demographicsgoldmine.com/category/demographics-2" title="View all posts in Demographics" rel="category tag">Demographics</a></span><br />
					<span class="comments">Comments <a href="http://demographicsgoldmine.com/have-you-been-focusing-on-the-baby-boom-market-all-these-years-three-ways-to-stay-on-top-of-markets#respond" title="Comment on Have you been focusing on the Baby Boom market all these years? Three ways to stay on top of markets.">(0)</a></span>					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
