			<div class="post-307 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-census-data">
				<!-- title, meta, and date info -->
				<div class="title clearfix">
					<div class="post-title">
						<h3 id="post-307"><a href="http://demographicsgoldmine.com/are-you-focused-only-on-your-swing-customers-what-you-need-to-know-about-your-customers-and-clients">Are You Focusing Only on Your “Swing” Customers?    What you need to know about your customers and clients</a></h3>
					</div>
					
					<div class="author-meta">
						by <span class="meta-author"><a href="http://demographicsgoldmine.com/author/Bob Scardamalia" title="Bob Scardamalia">Bob Scardamalia</a></span>					</div>
					
					<div class="post-meta">
						<span class="month">October</span>
						<span class="day">29<span class="day-suffix">th</span><span class="day-comma">,</span></span>
						<span class="year">2012</span><br />
					</div>
					</div>
				
				<!-- "Read More" link -->
				<div class="post-content">
					<p style="font-family: tahoma; font-size: 12pt; color: #0f2280;">It’s election season. The focus of the candidates and the pollsters is on the swing states because their demographics involve voters who may still be undecided.</p>
<p style="font-family: tahoma; font-size: 12pt; color: #0f2280;">When we listen to the polls in those swing states they break down the vote by the demographics.</p>
<p style="font-family: tahoma; font-size: 12pt; color: #0f2280;">
• &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Are there more young or old? Their interests in education, jobs, health care and retirement are different.<br />
• &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Do they live in rural or urban areas? Preservation of rural community life and dealing with congested urban housing are important.<br />
• &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Is the population a dominant minority and has it become more or less diverse?<br />
• &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Are there differences among males and females in lifestyle and employment?<br />
• &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Are there big income differentials that raise concerns over taxes and job opportunities?</p>
<p style="font-family: tahoma; font-size: 12pt; color: #0f2280;">All of these factors are important in an election and they’re important to your business or organization. Campaign managers are constantly looking at the data. Without data on the demographics and economic and social indicators, campaigns can’t target their message.  Imagine having only one message to deliver to such a diverse nation!</p>
<p><a href="http://demographicsgoldmine.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/minoritychange.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-310" title="minoritychange" src="http://demographicsgoldmine.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/minoritychange-300x224.png" alt="Census Map of Minority Change" width="300" height="224" /></a></p>
<p style="font-family: tahoma; font-size: 12pt; color: #0f2280;">Are you taking advantage of the data? Basic demographic data that are readily available — if you know where to look — can answer important questions to will help your business grow, understand your client’s needs, and help you target your message.  Without it, you&#8217;re making decisions in the dark.</p>
				</div>
				
				<!-- categories, tags and comments -->
